headline: NVIDIA’s Next Leg Higher May Have Started at CES
summary: NVIDIA is on track for a double-digit gain in 2026, which could reach the 90% range if factors, including sales to China, align.

headline: The AI question every job candidate on interview should be prepared to answer

headline: AI memory is sold out, causing an unprecedented surge in prices
summary: Three primary memory vendors — Micron, SK Hynix and Samsung Electronics — make up nearly the entire RAM market, and they're benefitting from this shortage.

headline: From SpaceX to Anthropic, 2026 Looks Like a Big Year for IPOs
summary: A pack of large private start-ups hungry for capital look ready to try a newly revived initial-public-offering market. SpaceX could be the largest, but AI companies could dominate the year.
